.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Flags \- Consensus flags
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Flags;
\&
\&        # full set of flags
\&        my $all_flags = Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Flags\->new;
\&
\&        # disable some flags (those not passed are active)
\&        my $some_flags = Bitcoin::Crypto::Transaction::Flags\->new(
\&                der_signatures => !!0,
\&        );
\&
\&        # use flags in transaction verification
\&        $transaction\->verify(flags => $some_flags);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a class that represents a set of consensus rules used in transaction
verification and associated systems. Each attribute of this class represents a
single rule.
.PP
By default, all implemented consensus rules are active, and all implemented
standardness rules are inactive when calling "new". As Bitcoin and this
module progress, more rules may be added all enabled by default on arrival.
Since Bitcoin is extended through softforks (implemented in a
backward\-compatible manner), this should rarely pose a problem with
Bitcoin::Crypto code. If you want to be extra sure, see "new_empty".
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
All the following flags are attributes available in the constructor of the
object. They have writer methods named \f(CW\*(C`set_X\*(C'\fR.
.SS "Consensus flags"
.IX Subsection "Consensus flags"
All consensus flags are active by default.
.PP
\fIp2sh\fR
.IX Subsection "p2sh"
.PP
Whether P2SH verification defined in
BIP16 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0016.mediawiki> should
be used.
.PP
\fIder_signatures\fR
.IX Subsection "der_signatures"
.PP
Whether strict DER signature verification defined in
BIP66 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0066.mediawiki> should
be used.
.PP
\fIchecklocktimeverify\fR
.IX Subsection "checklocktimeverify"
.PP
Whether \f(CW\*(C`OP_CHECKLOCKTIMEVERIFY\*(C'\fR opcode defined in
BIP65 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0065.mediawiki> should
be used.
.PP
\fIchecksequenceverify\fR
.IX Subsection "checksequenceverify"
.PP
Whether \f(CW\*(C`OP_CHECKSEQUENCEVERIFY\*(C'\fR opcode defined in
BIP112 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0112.mediawiki> should
be used.
.PP
\fInull_dummy\fR
.IX Subsection "null_dummy"
.PP
Whether \f(CW\*(C`OP_CHECKMULTISIG\*(C'\fR null dummy verification defined in
BIP147 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0147.mediawiki> should
be used.
.PP
\fIsegwit\fR
.IX Subsection "segwit"
.PP
Whether segwit\-specific verification defined in
BIP141 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0141.mediawiki> should
be used.
.PP
\fItaproot\fR
.IX Subsection "taproot"
.PP
Whether taproot\-specific verification defined in
BIP341 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0341.mediawiki> should
be used.
.SS "Standardness flags"
.IX Subsection "Standardness flags"
All standardness flags are inactive by default.
.PP
\fIsignature_pushes_only\fR
.IX Subsection "signature_pushes_only"
.PP
Disallows non\-push opcodes in signature scripts of inputs for legacy non\-P2SH
transactions. Automatically active for P2SH.
.PP
\fIminimal_if\fR
.IX Subsection "minimal_if"
.PP
Whether the argument to \f(CW\*(C`OP_IF\*(C'\fR must be minimal (\f(CW\*(C`OP_1\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`OP_0\*(C'\fR). Only
applicable to Segregated Witness scripts.
.PP
\fIcompressed_pubkeys\fR
.IX Subsection "compressed_pubkeys"
.PP
Whether public keys used is signature\-checking scripts must be compressed. Only
applicable to Segregated Witness scripts.
.PP
\fIstrict_encoding\fR
.IX Subsection "strict_encoding"
.PP
Disallows non\-strictly encoded DER signatures and public keys.
.PP
\fIlow_s_signatures\fR
.IX Subsection "low_s_signatures"
.PP
Disallows signatures encoded with low S.
.PP
\fIminimal_data\fR
.IX Subsection "minimal_data"
.PP
When active, data pushed by push opcodes must be minimally encoded.
.PP
\fInull_fail\fR
.IX Subsection "null_fail"
.PP
Causes non\-taproot signature\-checking opcodes to stop script execution on
failure, unless the signature is empty.
.PP
\fIclean_stack\fR
.IX Subsection "clean_stack"
.PP
Requires script stack to have exactly one element at the end of execution to
consider the execution successful.
.PP
\fIconst_script\fR
.IX Subsection "const_script"
.PP
Causes the script to fail if \f(CW\*(C`OP_CODESEPARATOR\*(C'\fR or a signature is encoded in a
pre\-SegWit script.
.PP
\fIknown_witness\fR
.IX Subsection "known_witness"
.PP
Causes the transaction verification to fail if unknown version of Segregated
Witness program is encountered.
.PP
\fIillegal_upgradeable_nops\fR
.IX Subsection "illegal_upgradeable_nops"
.PP
Disallows the use of \f(CW\*(C`OP_NOPX\*(C'\fR opcodes (but not \f(CW\*(C`OP_NOP\*(C'\fR).
.SS Methods
.IX Subsection "Methods"
\fInew\fR
.IX Subsection "new"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $object = $class\->new(%args)
.Ve
.PP
This is a standard Moo constructor, which can be used to create the object. It
takes arguments specified in "Consensus flags" and "Standardness flags".
.PP
Returns a class instance.
.PP
\fInew_empty\fR
.IX Subsection "new_empty"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $object = $class\->new_empty(%args)
.Ve
.PP
Same as "new", but assumes all flags unspecified in \f(CW%args\fR are disabled.
.PP
\fInew_full\fR
.IX Subsection "new_full"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $object = $class\->new_full(%args)
.Ve
.PP
Same as "new", but assumes all flags unspecified in \f(CW%args\fR are enabled.
.PP
\fIstrict_signatures\fR
.IX Subsection "strict_signatures"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $bool = $object\->strict_signatures()
.Ve
.PP
Return true if any one of "strict_encoding", "der_signatures" or
"low_s_signatures" are enabled. Having either one of these flags in effect is
the same as having "der_signatures" enabled.
